"My next call, by the end of this year, we're near 40 dollars a barrel in WTI crude."

Two reasons from Mike McGlone: a record supply glut in the Western Hemisphere, and Trump needing lower prices before the midterms because affordability is the top issue. WTI has traded the same range for 20 years and it's at the top of it now.

